The paper is about the query language Cypher, which is used in graph databases. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper provides denotational semantics for Cypher, which is a formal approach to understanding the meaning of programming languages. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, as denotational semantics is often used in the study of programming languages in the context of machine learning. The paper also deals with pattern matching and filtering, which are common operations in data structures and algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the read-only part of Cypher, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category, as it deals with the design and implementation of a specific programming language. The paper could also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category, as it deals with the formal semantics of a specific programming language.
